feat: Add FlatBuffers support for SyncUploadFileInfo and enhance IPC message handling
- Introduced FlatBuffers schema for upload file information. - Implemented serialization and deserialization methods in Lusp_SyncFilesNotificationService. - Updated Lusp_AsioLoopbackIpcClient to send messages with a length prefix for better IPC communication. - Modified CMake configuration for improved build settings and environment management. - Added a new CLEANUP_GUIDE.txt for project cleanup instructions.

Add FlatBuffers support for file upload information
- Introduced a new FlatBuffer schema for upload file information in `upload_file_info_generated.h`. - Updated `Lusp_AsioLoopbackIpcServer` to handle FlatBuffer messages, allowing for structured data processing. - Modified the server's message handling to differentiate between FlatBuffer and regular string messages. - Enhanced the main server loop to process FlatBuffer messages and extract relevant fields for logging. - Updated `Lusp_SyncUploadFileInfoHandler` to include new methods for handling file information with FlatBuffers. - Adjusted client-side IPC communication to log messages sent over the socket. - Improved logging in `Lusp_SyncFilesNotificationService` to support wide character output for file names.
